author: Daniel Lippman
title: Trump administration weighs lifting coronavirus aid freeze
description: Agencies are discussing a draft presidential memorandum outlining the proposal, which has yet to land on the president’s desk.
content:
He announced that the U.S. would devote an additional $225 million in health, humanitarian and economic assistance to help other countries respond to the virus -- on top of some $274 million the U.S. already has committed.
